There are a number of changes that needed to be made:

- The radio groups were being used incorrectly; radio buttons that belong to the same group need the same name or else multiple radios can be selected for one group

- You need to define a global variable to pass values between different scopes the way you were doing (for example `priceofpizza` doesn&#39;t exits in the scope of `onclick`  you used on your `&lt;button&gt;` element), I went ahead and handled this by declaring a `global`/`window` variable called `model`

- You need to actually retrieve the values of the input using the DOM (`document`)


```html
